{"type":"session_message","session_id":"ses_28a77699cffeNuNcQOA57Lb5pD","role":"assistant","message_id":"msg_d758896ea001Wr7PORDX3FMJ1p","parts":[{"id":"prt_d7588a6a1001TCwn8HQ1vTLO7h","messageID":"msg_d758896ea001Wr7PORDX3FMJ1p","sessionID":"ses_28a77699cffeNuNcQOA57Lb5pD","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_d251a26c0904460595b194ea","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/README.rst"},"output":"<path>/workspace/README.rst</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: |  |downloads| |stars| |forks| |contributors|\n2: |  |version| |packages| |license|\n3: |  |github-actions| |doc| |twitter|\n4: \n5: .. |downloads| image:: https://img.shields.io/pypi/dm/pyftpdlib.svg\n6:     :target: https://pepy.tech/project/pyftpdlib\n7:     :alt: Downloads\n8: \n9: .. |stars| image:: https://img.shields.io/github/stars/giampaolo/pyftpdlib.svg\n10:     :target: https://github.com/giampaolo/pyftpdlib/stargazers\n11:     :alt: Github stars\n12: \n13: .. |forks| image:: https://img.shields.io/github/forks/giampaolo/pyftpdlib.svg\n14:     :target: https://github.com/giampaolo/pyftpdlib/network/members\n15:     :alt: Github forks\n16: \n17: .. |contributors| image:: https://img.shields.io/github/contributors/giampaolo/pyftpdlib.svg\n18:     :target: https://github.com/giampaolo/pyftpdlib/graphs/contributors\n19:     :alt: Contributors\n20: \n21: .. |github-actions| image:: https://img.shields.io/github/actions/workflow/status/giampaolo/pyftpdlib/.github/workflows/tests.yml\n22:     :target: https://github.com/giampaolo/pyftpdlib/actions\n23:     :alt: GH actions\n24: \n25: .. |doc| image:: https://readthedocs.org/projects/pyftpdlib/badge/?version=latest\n26:     :target: https://pyftpdlib.readthedocs.io/en/latest/\n27:     :alt: Documentation Status\n28: \n29: .. |version| image:: https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/pyftpdlib.svg?label=pypi\n30:     :target: https://pypi.org/project/pyftpdlib\n31:     :alt: Latest version\n32: \n33: .. |py-versions| image:: https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/psutil.svg\n34:     :alt: Supported Python versions\n35: \n36: .. |packages| image:: https://repology.org/badge/tiny-repos/python:pyftpdlib.svg\n37:     :target: https://repology.org/metapackage/python:pyftpdlib/versions\n38:     :alt: Binary packages\n39: \n40: .. |license| image:: https://img.shields.io/github/license/giampaolo/pyftpdlib\n41:     :target: https://github.com/giampaolo/pyftpdlib/blob/master/LICENSE\n42:     :alt: License\n43: \n44: .. |twitter| image:: https://img.shields.io/twitter/follow/grodola?style=flat\n45:     :target: https://twitter.com/grodola\n46:     :alt: Twitter Follow\n47: \n48: Quick links\n49: ===========\n50: \n51: - `Home`_\n52: - `Documentation`_\n53: - `Download`_\n54: - `Mailing list`_\n55: - `What's new`_\n56: \n57: About\n58: =====\n59: \n60: Python FTP server library provides a high-level portable interface to easily\n61: write very efficient, scalable and asynchronous FTP servers with Python. It is\n62: the most complete `RFC-959`_ FTP server implementation available for the\n63: `Python`_ programming language.\n64: \n65: Features\n66: ========\n67: \n68: - Extremely **lightweight**, **fast** and **scalable** (see\n69:   `why <https://github.com/giampaolo/pyftpdlib/issues/203>`__ and\n70:   `benchmarks`_).\n71: - Uses **sendfile(2)** (see `pysendfile <https://github.com/giampaolo/pysendfile>`__)\n72:   system call for uploads (Linux only).\n73: - Uses ``epoll()`` / ``kqueue()`` / ``select()`` to handle concurrency\n74:   asynchronously.\n75: - ...But can optionally skip to a `multiple thread / process`_ model (as in:\n76:   you'll be free to block or use slow filesystems).\n77: - Portable: entirely written in pure Python.\n78: - Supports **FTPS** (`RFC-4217`_), **IPv6** (`RFC-2428`_), **Unicode** file\n79:   names (`RFC-2640`_), **MLSD/MLST** commands (`RFC-3659`_).\n80: - Support for virtual users and virtual filesystem.\n81: - Flexible system of \"authorizers\" able to manage both \"virtual\" and\n82:   \"real\" users on on both\n83:   `UNIX <https://pyftpdlib.readthedocs.io/en/latest/tutorial.html#unix-ftp-server>`__\n84:   and\n85:   `Windows <https://pyftpdlib.readthedocs.io/en/latest/tutorial.html#windows-ftp-server>`__.\n86: \n87: Performance\n88: ===========\n89: \n90: Despite being written in an interpreted language, pyftpdlib has transfer rates\n91: comparable or superior to common UNIX FTP servers written in C. It usually\n92: tends to scale better (see `benchmarks`_) because whereas vsftpd and proftpd\n93: use multiple processes to achieve concurrency, pyftpdlib only uses one (see\n94: `the C10K problem`_).\n95: \n96: pyftpdlib vs. proftpd 1.3.4\n97: ---------------------------\n98: \n99: +-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n100: | **benchmark type**                      | **pyftpdlib**  | **proftpd**    | **speedup** |\n101: +-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n102: | STOR (client -> server)                 |  585.90 MB/sec | 600.49 MB/sec  | -0.02x      |\n103: +-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n104: | RETR (server -> client)                 | 1652.72 MB/sec | 1524.05 MB/sec | **+0.08**   |\n105: +-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n106: | 300 concurrent clients (connect, login) |    0.19 secs   | 9.98 secs      | **+51x**    |\n107: +-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n108: | STOR (1 file with 300 idle clients)     |  585.59 MB/sec | 518.55 MB/sec  | **+0.1x**   |\n109: +-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n110: | RETR (1 file with 300 idle clients)     | 1497.58 MB/sec | 1478.19 MB/sec | 0x          |\n111: +-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n112: | 300 concurrent clients (RETR 10M file)  |    3.41 secs   | 3.60 secs      | **+0.05x**  |\n113: +-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n114: | 300 concurrent clients (STOR 10M file)  |    8.60 secs   | 11.56 secs     | **+0.3x**   |\n115: +-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n116: | 300 concurrent clients (QUIT)           |    0.03 secs   | 0.39 secs      | **+12x**    |\n117: +-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n118: \n119: pyftpdlib vs. vsftpd 2.3.5\n120: --------------------------\n121: \n122: +-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n123: | **benchmark type**                      | **pyftpdlib**  | **vsftpd**     | **speedup** |\n124: +-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n125: | STOR (client -> server)                 |  585.90 MB/sec | 611.73 MB/sec  | -0.04x      |\n126: +-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n127: | RETR (server -> client)                 | 1652.72 MB/sec | 1512.92 MB/sec | **+0.09**   |\n128: +-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n129: | 300 concurrent clients (connect, login) |    0.19 secs   | 20.39 secs     | **+106x**   |\n130: +-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n131: | STOR (1 file with 300 idle clients)     |  585.59 MB/sec | 610.23 MB/sec  | -0.04x      |\n132: +-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n133: | RETR (1 file with 300 idle clients)     | 1497.58 MB/sec | 1493.01 MB/sec | 0x          |\n134: +-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n135: | 300 concurrent clients (RETR 10M file)  |    3.41 secs   | 3.67 secs      | **+0.07x**  |\n136: +-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n137: | 300 concurrent clients (STOR 10M file)  |    8.60 secs   | 9.82 secs      | **+0.07x**  |\n138: +-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n139: | 300 concurrent clients (QUIT)           |    0.03 secs   | 0.01 secs      | +0.14x      |\n140: +-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n141: \n142: For more benchmarks see `here <https://pyftpdlib.readthedocs.io/en/latest/benchmarks.html>`__.\n143: \n144: Command line usage\n145: ==================\n146: \n147: Start an anonymous FTP server on port 2121:\n148: \n149: .. code-block:: sh\n150: \n151:     $ python3 -m pyftpdlib\n152:     [I 2024-06-23 13:49:35] >>> starting FTP server on 0.0.0.0:2121, pid=763634 <<<\n153: \n154: Same but with write permissions (useful to setup a quick and dirty file sharing server):\n155: \n156: .. code-block:: sh\n157: \n158:     $ python3 -m pyftpdlib --write\n159:     [I 2024-06-23 13:49:35] >>> starting FTP server on 0.0.0.0:2121, pid=763641 <<<\n160: \n161: Also see `CLI doc <https://pyftpdlib.readthedocs.io/en/latest/cli.html>`__\n162: for more command line examples.\n163: \n164: API usage\n165: =========\n166: \n167: .. code-block:: python\n168: \n169:     >>> from pyftpdlib.authorizers import DummyAuthorizer\n170:     >>> from pyftpdlib.handlers import FTPHandler\n171:     >>> from pyftpdlib.servers import FTPServer\n172:     >>>\n173:     >>> authorizer = DummyAuthorizer()\n174:     >>> authorizer.add_user(\"user\", \"12345\", \"/home/giampaolo\", perm=\"elradfmwMT\")\n175:     >>> authorizer.add_anonymous(\"/home/nobody\")\n176:     >>>\n177:     >>> handler = FTPHandler\n178:     >>> handler.authorizer = authorizer\n179:     >>>\n180:     >>> server = FTPServer((\"127.0.0.1\", 21), handler)\n181:     >>> server.serve_forever()\n182:     [I 13-02-19 10:55:42] >>> starting FTP server on 127.0.0.1:21 <<<\n183:     [I 13-02-19 10:55:42] poller: <class 'pyftpdlib.ioloop.Epoll'>\n184:     [I 13-02-19 10:55:42] masquerade (NAT) address: None\n185:     [I 13-02-19 10:55:42] passive ports: None\n186:     [I 13-02-19 10:55:42] use sendfile(2): True\n187:     [I 13-02-19 10:55:45] 127.0.0.1:34178-[] FTP session opened (connect)\n188:     [I 13-02-19 10:55:48] 127.0.0.1:34178-[user] USER 'user' logged in.\n189:     [I 13-02-19 10:56:27] 127.0.0.1:34179-[user] RETR /home/giampaolo/.vimrc completed=1 bytes=1700 seconds=0.001\n190:     [I 13-02-19 10:56:39] 127.0.0.1:34179-[user] FTP session closed (disconnect).\n191: \n192: For other code samples read the `tutorial <https://pyftpdlib.readthedocs.io/en/latest/tutorial.html>`__\n193: \n194: Donate\n195: ======\n196: \n197: A lot of time and effort went into making pyftpdlib as it is right now.\n198: If you feel pyftpdlib is useful to you or your business and want to support its\n199: future development please consider `donating`_ me some money.\n200: \n201: .. _`benchmarks`: https://pyftpdlib.readthedocs.io/en/latest/benchmarks.html\n202: .. _`Documentation`: https://pyftpdlib.readthedocs.io\n203: .. _`donating`: https://gmpy.dev/donate\n204: .. _`Download`: https://pypi.org/project/pyftpdlib/\n205: .. _`Home`: https://github.com/giampaolo/pyftpdlib\n206: .. _`Mailing list`: https://groups.google.com/group/pyftpdlib/topics\n207: .. _`multiple thread / process`: https://pyftpdlib.readthedocs.io/en/latest/tutorial.html#changing-the-concurrency-model\n208: .. _`Python`: https://www.python.org/\n209: .. _`RFC-2428`: https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc2428\n210: .. _`RFC-2640`: https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc2640\n211: .. _`RFC-3659`: https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc3659\n212: .. _`RFC-4217`: https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc4217\n213: .. _`RFC-959`: https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc959.html\n214: .. _`the C10K problem`: http://www.kegel.com/c10k.html\n215: .. _`What's new`: https://github.com/giampaolo/pyftpdlib/blob/master/HISTORY.rst\n\n(End of file - total 215 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"|  |downloads| |stars| |forks| |contributors|\n|  |version| |packages| |license|\n|  |github-actions| |doc| |twitter|\n\n.. |downloads| image:: https://img.shields.io/pypi/dm/pyftpdlib.svg\n    :target: https://pepy.tech/project/pyftpdlib\n    :alt: Downloads\n\n.. |stars| image:: https://img.shields.io/github/stars/giampaolo/pyftpdlib.svg\n    :target: https://github.com/giampaolo/pyftpdlib/stargazers\n    :alt: Github stars\n\n.. |forks| image:: https://img.shields.io/github/forks/giampaolo/pyftpdlib.svg\n    :target: https://github.com/giampaolo/pyftpdlib/network/members\n    :alt: Github forks\n\n.. |contributors| image:: https://img.shields.io/github/contributors/giampaolo/pyftpdlib.svg\n    :target: https://github.com/giampaolo/pyftpdlib/graphs/contributors\n    :alt: Contributors\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"README.rst","time":{"start":1775793383412,"end":1775793383423}}}]}
